### 2. Plural form interception — `src/lib/list-command.ts`

`interceptSubcommand()` (line 391) checks if a positional arg is a known subcommand name. It builds the set via `getSubcommandsForRoute()` which only collects `child.name.original` from Stricli's `getAllEntries()`.

**Verify** whether Stricli's `getAllEntries()` includes alias entries. If it does, `ls` is automatically recognized. If it doesn't, update `getSubcommandsForRoute()` to also collect aliases from each child entry (they expose `readonly aliases: readonly string[]`).

This ensures `sentry issues ls` (plural form + alias) correctly prints the tip and auto-detects instead of treating `ls` as an org slug.

